### Infrastructure Error Recovery

```yaml
# Error recovery strategies for infrastructure failures
Database Connection Failure:
  - Retry connection up to 3 times with 5-second delays
  - Check if database container is running
  - Verify network connectivity
  - Fall back to in-memory database for unit tests

Redis Connection Failure:
  - Retry connection up to 3 times with 5-second delays
  - Skip Redis-dependent tests if unavailable
  - Use in-memory cache for testing

NATS Connection Failure:
  - Retry connection up to 3 times with 5-second delays
  - Use mock NATS client for unit tests
  - Skip integration tests if unavailable

Docker Compose Failure:
  - Check Docker daemon is running
  - Verify docker-compose.yml syntax
  - Check port conflicts
  - Provide clear error messages with resolution steps
```

## Testing Strategy

### Test Pyramid Structure

The testing strategy follows the test pyramid principle:

```
        /\
       /  \
      / E2E \          ~20 tests (Critical user flows)
     /--------\
    /          \
   / Integration \     ~200 tests (Service interactions)
  /--------------\
 /                \
/   Unit Tests     \   ~1000 tests (Functions, components)
--------------------
```

### Testing Approach by Layer

#### Unit Tests (Base Layer)

**Scope**: Individual functions, components, methods, and classes in isolation

**Tools**:
- Frontend: Vitest + React Testing Library
- Backend: Go test + testify

**Coverage Target**: ≥80% line coverage, ≥70% branch coverage

**Execution Time**: <30 seconds for full suite

**Test Organization**:
```
Frontend:
  src/
    components/
      Button.tsx
      __tests__/
        Button.test.tsx
    hooks/
      useApi.ts
      __tests__/
        useApi.test.ts

Backend:
  internal/
    handlers/
      auth_handler.go
      auth_handler_test.go
    services/
      auth_service.go
      auth_service_test.go
```

**Example Unit Test (Frontend)**:
```typescript
// src/components/__tests__/Button.test.tsx
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest';
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';
import { Button } from '../Button';

describe('Button', () => {
  it('should render with correct text', () => {
    render(<Button>Click me</Button>);
    expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'Click me' })).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it('should call onClick handler when clicked', async () => {
    const handleClick = vi.fn();
    render(<Button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</Button>);
    
    await userEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button'));
    
    expect(handleClick).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });

  it('should be disabled when disabled prop is true', () => {
    render(<Button disabled>Click me</Button>);
    expect(screen.getByRole('button')).toBeDisabled();
  });
});
```

**Example Unit Test (Backend)**:
```go
// internal/handlers/auth_handler_test.go
package handlers

import (
    "bytes"
    "encoding/json"
    "net/http"
    "net/http/httptest"
    "testing"
    
    "github.com/stretchr/testify/assert"
    "github.com/stretchr/testify/mock"
)

func TestAuthHandler_Login(t *testing.T) {
    tests := []struct {
        name           string
        requestBody    map[string]string
        mockResponse   *User
        mockError      error
        expectedStatus int
    }{
        {
            name: "successful login",
            requestBody: map[string]string{
                "email":    "test@example.com",
                "password": "password123",
            },
            mockResponse: &User{
                ID:    "user-123",
                Email: "test@example.com",
            },
            mockError:      nil,
            expectedStatus: http.StatusOK,
        },
        {
            name: "invalid credentials",
            requestBody: map[string]string{
                "email":    "test@example.com",
                "password": "wrong",
            },
            mockResponse:   nil,
            mockError:      ErrInvalidCredentials,
            expectedStatus: http.StatusUnauthorized,
        },
    }
    
    for _, tt := range tests {
        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {
            // Arrange
            mockService := new(MockAuthService)
            mockService.On("Login", mock.Anything, tt.requestBody["email"], tt.requestBody["password"]).
                Return(tt.mockResponse, tt.mockError)
            
            handler := NewAuthHandler(mockService)
            
            body, _ := json.Marshal(tt.requestBody)
            req := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodPost, "/auth/login", bytes.NewBuffer(body))
            req.Header.Set("Content-Type", "application/json")
            rr := httptest.NewRecorder()
            
            // Act
            handler.Login(rr, req)
            
            // Assert
            assert.Equal(t, tt.expectedStatus, rr.Code)
            mockService.AssertExpectations(t)
        })
    }
}
```

